Interface IHost

All Superinterfaces:
IManagedObjectRef, android.os.Parcelable, TreeNode
public interface IHost
extends IManagedObjectRef, android.os.Parcelable, TreeNode

The IHost interface represents the physical machine that this VirtualBox installation runs on. An object implementing this interface is returned by the IVirtualBox.getHost() attribute. This interface contains read-only information about the host's physical hardware (such as what processors and disks are available, what the host operating system is, and so on) and also allows for manipulating some of the host's hardware, such as global USB device filters and host interface networking.
